The paper deals with the problem of pairwise energy minimization, which is a common problem in computer vision and machine learning. The paper proposes a new sufficient condition for partial optimality, which is a fundamental problem in artificial intelligence and optimization. The paper also proposes a polynomial method for finding the maximum optimal partial assignment, which involves linear programming and graph algorithms, indicating that the paper may belong to the categories of computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves graph algorithms and optimization, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
